eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.utils

Class Mapping

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.slipo.athenarc.triplegeo.utils.Mapping

  • public class Mapping
extends java.lang.Object
    Retains mappings of feature attributes (input) to RDF predicates (output) that will be used in generation of triples.
    Version:
    1.8
    Author:
    Kostas Patroumpas

        public void createFromFile(java.lang.String fileName)
        Creates a new mapping specification from a YML file. This file specifies mappings from attribute names of the input to RDF properties in the output triples.
        Parameters:
        fileName - Path to the YML file.

      • findMultiFaceted

        public java.lang.String findMultiFaceted(java.lang.String key)
        Identifies whether a multi-faceted attribute is included in the mapping specifications.
        Parameters:
        key - The name of the attribute as used in the dataset.
        Returns:
        The name of its corresponding multi-faceted attribute in the mapping, i.e., without the suffix following the wild char '%' in the specification.
